    • merge

      @Nonnull public FloatMatrix merge(@Nonnull Grid<Float> g, @Nonnull BinaryOperator<Float> f) throws IllegalArgumentException
      Merges this grid with another grid of the same dimensions. The merger function f is applied to each component, and the resulting grid is returned.

      For example, if a sum function (x, y) -> x + y was provided, this would return the sum of the two grids of numbers. This is just an example, and matrices should be used for arithmetic operations.

      Specified by:
      merge in interface Grid<Float>
      Parameters:
      g - The other grid to merge with
      f - The merger function to apply
      Returns:
      The resulting grid
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - When the provided grid g's dimensions do not match to this grid's dimensions
